ble. <br><br>We are ALL for it here at Cliphair, so we’ve come up with some super quick &amp; easy Hairstyles to liven up your laidback look. We’ve chosen 3 of our favourite “No heat, low effort” styles to share with you!
<br>
<br>Even though all of these hair-dos can be created with or without using hair extensions, they can all be enhanced by using any of our items from our <a href="https://www.cliphair.co.uk/collections/supreme-quad-weft" target="_self">One Piece Hair Extensions Collection</a> or our Hair pieces (Fringe or Ponytail). With all of these hair extensions being applied in under 3 minutes wed say that’s definitely sticking to the theme of Minimum effort, Maximum style!&nbsp;&nbsp;<br></span></p></div></div><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-gXRojI kCnmwO pf-24_"><div title="washing hair extensions" data-pf-type="Image" class="sc-iWBNLc NncQz pf-25_"><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0069/6470/7389/t/9/assets/pf-e38b3d56--1_1200x.png?v=1611929386" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0069/6470/7389/t/9/assets/pf-e38b3d56--1.png?v=1611929386 1536w" width="279" height="466" sizes="(min-width: 1536px) 1536px, (min-width: 1024px) 1280px, (min-width: 640px) 768px, 320px" loading="lazy" alt="washing hair extensions" title="washing hair extensions"/></div></div></div></div></div></div><div data-section-id="pf-8de4" data-pf-type="Section" class="sc-igXgud lhtyiH pf-26_"><div style="--cw:1170px" class="sc-cjrPHo eOcrMz"><div class="sc-jgrJph iGtnpe pf-27_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:0px;--s-sm:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-gXRojI kCnmwO pf-28_"><h2 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-bSqaIl iXTDAP pf-29_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-BHvUt fJlZte pf-31_">LOUNGE LOOK ONE– The Messy French Braid<br></span></h2></div></div></div><div class="sc-jgrJph iGtnpe pf-32_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:0px;--s-sm:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-gXRojI kCnmwO pf-33_"><p class="sc-ehIJor eZpnKY pf-34_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-BHvUt fJlZte pf-36_"><span style="font-weight: bold;">Step 1
<br></span>Give your hair a good brush. Loosely put your hair into your normal parting. 
<br><span style="font-weight: bold;">Step 2 
<br></span>Grab 3 pieces of hair from just under your crown, for a chunky braid take thick pieces for a neater one take finer pieces. Start your braid by weaving the strands under and over each other like you would in a normal braid. 
<br><span style="font-weight: bold;">Step 3 
<br></span>Once you have done your first step of the normal braid with each new weave grab another piece of hair that sits next to that piece and add it in to that strand. Continue this pattern until you have reached halfway down your hair. I like to leave ¼ of the hair after the nape of your neck un-braided for an even quicker but just as stylish look!
<br><span style="font-weight: bold;">Step 4 
<br></span>Before you tie the end of the braid, whilst holding it together use your other hand to gently pull the braid out a little starting from the top. You don’t want to completely undo your braid; you are just pulling to loosen it which will also make your hair seem thicker. 
<br><span style="font-weight: bold;">Step 5 
<br></span>Secure the end with a hair tie, then tighten it by pulling the underneath hair apart. Pull some hair out around your face and above your ears, use your hands to slightly scrunch the top of your hair to give a little texture. You can also use a texture spray on the ends at the same time as slightly rubbing the hair if your hair is very straight/fly-away to give even more of a messy effect. <br><br>
For some extra oopmpg, add one of our one piece hair extensions in just before step 2&nbsp; to make this look even thicker and longer. Try using a lighter shade than your hair to give your braid a pop of colour!&nbsp;<br><p> </p></span></p></div></div></div><div class="sc-jgrJph iGtnpe pf-37_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-gXRojI kCnmwO pf-38_"><div title="washing hair extensions" data-pf-type="Image" class="sc-iWBNLc NncQz pf-39_"><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0069/6470/7389/t/9/assets/pf-8b3d56b9--2_1200x.png?v=1611929423" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0069/6470/7389/t/9/assets/pf-8b3d56b9--2.png?v=1611929423 1536w" width="300" height="447" sizes="(min-width: 1536px) 1536px, (min-width: 1024px) 1280px, (min-width: 640px) 768px, 320px" loading="lazy" alt="washing hair extensions" title="washing hair extensions"/></div></div></div></div><div class="sc-jgrJph iGtnpe pf-40_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-gXRojI kCnmwO pf-41_"><h2 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-bSqaIl iXTDAP pf-42_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-BHvUt fJlZte pf-44_">LOUNGE LOOK TWO – The Sleek Low Pony<br></span></h2></div></div><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-gXRojI kCnmwO pf-45_"><p class="sc-ehIJor eZpnKY pf-46_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-BHvUt fJlZte pf-48_"><span style="font-weight: bold;">Step 1
<br></span>Give your hair a good brush and spritz with a little moisture spray, if you haven’t got any moisture spray serum/hair oil on the ends will do the trick. 
<br><span style="font-weight: bold;">Step 2 
<br></span>Neatly separate your hair into your normal parting. Using your brush to neaten stray hairs scoop your hair into a low ponytail just above the nape of your neck. Secure the pony with a hair band. 
<br><span style="font-weight: bold;">Step 3 
<br></span>Take a inch thick piece of hair from your ponytail underneath the hair band. Wrap this around the hair band and secure tightly with a few hair grips, I prefer to secure the strand underneath my pony to keep the grips hidden. 
<br><span style="font-weight: bold;">Step 4 
<br></span>Give your hair a final spritz of hairspray to give it a little shine and catch any fly away hairs around the face. <br><br>
