<br></span>Part your hair where you would usually wear it. Scoop your hair into a loose, low ponytail and secure with a hairband. 
<br><span style="font-weight: bold;">Step 2
<br></span>Before you make the bun, using both hands slightly pull outwards at the hair just above the hairband to loosen the ponytail. Separate your ponytail into 2 even sections. 
<br><span style="font-weight: bold;">Step 3
<br></span>Twirl the 2 sections around each other from the top to bottom. Keeping hold of the end of the twirled hair, wrap it into a circle around the top of the ponytail (hairband area) and secure around the edges of the bun with hair pins making sure the hairband is hidden.  
<br><span style="font-weight: bold;">Step 4 
<br></span>Pull some hair out from around the front of your face, and scrunch the roots of your hair with your fingers to give the top some texture. Finish with a little texture spray to secure the bun. <br><br>
